      <accessrestrict id="aspace_3713e2ec80071195f275c78e5a8de0d5">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>This collection is open for research.</p>
      </accessrestrict>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_d4b839fdde343259c8a8d157660d2e5a">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Purchased from McBride Rare Books on the Louis Mayer Rabinowitz Memorial Fund, 2023 and from Andover Street Archives on the Walter Jennings Memorial Fund, 2023.</p>
      </acqinfo>
      <arrangement id="aspace_ac75db848e9f9ec9608552bc44e70f5d">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>This collection is arranged in two series: I. September 2023 Acquisition, 1948-1957. II. November 2023 Acquisition, circa 1966-1969.</p>
      </arrangement>
      <bioghist id="aspace_0aae46cb4d8f50a91a93e9adf88152df">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>This assembled collection contains small groups of archival materials including memos, leaflets, letters, fliers, and other documentation related to antidraft and pacifism movements in the United States.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <prefercite id="aspace_4ed23ec9a03e5a52451da270085f80f3">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Cold War Antidraft and Pacifism Collection. General Collection, Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library, Yale University.</p>
      </prefercite>
      <processinfo id="aspace_53bf8d670a79b02ebebee09a3aff3d94">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Collections are processed to a variety of levels, depending on the work necessary to make them usable, their perceived research value, the availability of staff, competing priorities, and whether or not further accruals are expected.  The library attempts to provide a basic level of preservation and access for all collections, and does more extensive processing of higher priority collections as time and resources permit.</p>
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_634390b3a86db8b955ec98816aa42faa">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection contains small groups of archival materials related to antidraft and pacifism movements in the United States including memos, leaflets, letters, fliers, and other documents.</p>
      </scopecontent>
